The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Saturday, January 18, 2003 				Metro Recommends
				 																THE meet				 																																	(Kalamandir, Jan. 21, 6 pm)				 																																	l President A.P.J. Abdul Kalam will deliver the Platinum Jubilee Address of the Indian Chamber of Commerce (ICC), at the ICCs 75th annual general meeting. Cards are available on a first-come first-served basis at the ICC office from Saturday				 																THE CONCERT				 																																	(Sukanta Sadan, Barrackpore, 7 pm)				 																																	lThe night-long classical festival will feature the likes of Ustad Shahid Parvez on sitar, Pandit Tarun Bhattacharya on santoor and Pandit Ronu Majumdar on flute. Bikram Ghosh, Subhankar Banerjee and Ramkumar Mishra are among the accompanists				 																THE CD				 																																	(Santana)				 																																	lThis two-CD set combines the magic of the early Santana band live in Munich, Paris and London with new songs recorded in San Francisco. The guitar guru strikes the perfect chord with Tom Coster on his Yamaha Electric Grand and Hammond Organ				 																THE BOOK				 																																	(Kevin Rushby)				 																																	lThe author of Hunting Pirate Heaven explores the dark side of India in this book. Part history and part personal record, it reveals how British India demonised millions as hereditary criminals, setting off a witch-hunt whose effects are still felt today
